4. Mobile Mockup Descriptions

Design language: card-based, minimal, lots of white space, one accent color, big rounded corners (16–20px), soft shadows, bottom-sheet interactions. Think Beli's social clarity + Citymapper's transit density restraint.

5. Home / Dashboard


Top: greeting + today's weather chip + a "Plan a new day" primary button (full-width, accent).
Section "Your Ventures": horizontal carousel of venture cards (cover map thumbnail, title, date, total cost badge, stop count).
Section "Continue planning": drafts.
Section "From your feed": 2–3 public ventures you might copy.
Bottom tab bar (see nav).


7. Venture Builder (hero screen)

Vertical split:


Top 40% — live map with numbered pins + polyline route. Collapses to a thin strip on scroll.
Summary bar (sticky, between map and cards): four pill metrics — ⏱ Drive 1h 12m · 💵 $84 · ⛽ $11 · ☀️ 72°. These animate/recount on reorder.
Bottom 60% — draggable card list. Each card: drag handle, order number, place name, category icon, address line, $ est + ⏱ dur chips, notes preview. Long-press → lift + reorder; release → metrics recompute with a subtle shimmer.
Floating + Add stop button.
Sticky footer: Save private / Publish.


8/9. Add / Edit Card

Bottom sheet: place autocomplete (Location/Google), category selector (coffee, food, museum, view, nightlife, niche…), estimated cost stepper, duration stepper, notes field. Edit reuses the same sheet pre-filled, plus delete.

10. Route Map (full-screen)

Full map, numbered stops, tap a pin → mini card peek, leg-by-leg drive times along the polyline, recenter + "open in Maps" buttons.

11. Budget Breakdown

Donut chart (food / activities / gas / misc) + line-item list per stop showing estimated vs (later) actual. Total at top, "per person" toggle.

12. Weather Detail

Hour-by-hour strip aligned to the schedule — so each stop shows the forecast for the time you'll be there (key differentiator). Sunset time highlighted for "sunset lookout" stops.

13. Schedule / Timeline

Vertical timeline: arrival → activity duration → drive leg → next arrival, with clock times. Drag here also reorders.

14/15. Ideation Folders


Folders list: grid of folder cards (name, item count, last-saved thumbnail collage).
Folder detail: grid of saved link cards — platform icon (TikTok/IG), thumbnail placeholder, caption snippet, saved date. Tap → opens original link externally. Multi-select → "Turn into venture" (later).


16. Save Link

Two entry points: (a) OS share sheet — user shares a TikTok/IG video → Trek appears as a target → folder picker bottom sheet → save URL only. (b) In-app "+ Save link" → paste URL → pick folder. No scraping; we store the canonical URL + platform + savedAt.

18. Discover Feed

Beli-style vertical feed of PublicVenturePosts. Each post card: cover = map route preview, title + tags (date night, food crawl…), author avatar/handle, overall day rating (★), 3–4 stacked stop thumbnails, like/comment/save counts, prominent "Copy route" button. Filter bar on top: tags, area, rating, distance.

19. Public Venture Detail


Header: map route preview + caption + tags + overall ★ + author.
Stops list in order: each expandable stop = photos carousel, place name + category, user rating ★, review text, "would recommend" chip, cost.
Sticky footer: ❤️ Like · 💬 Comment · 🔖 Save · ➕ Copy to my planner.
Copy spawns a private editable venture pre-filled with all stops.


21/22. Publish + Per-Stop Review Composer

Publish flow: pick which completed venture → for each stop, composer (star rating, review text, photo upload, actual cost, wouldVisitAgain toggle, visitedAt) → overall day rating → caption → tags → visibility (public) → post.
